{
  "stem": "13469.7",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I found out only yesterday, I think, by reading some of these letters, that my aunt in Israel also offered to take us in, in Palestine, at that time.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I don't think we ever actually really knew it, or we decided on England, really.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We, we liked England the first time, and we always believed England was the right place for us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we always heard good things about England.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We liked the looks of England.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not really.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- my uncle and aunt lived in northwest Dollis Hill, in a flat, block of flats, 60 flats.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it wasn't very big.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [NON-ENGLISH] and [NON-ENGLISH], they had two children of their own by that time-- Peter and Ruth, usually referred to as [NON-ENGLISH] sustained from [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So with an extra three children, the flat wasn't nearly big enough, kind of thing, so they had great difficulties.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nevertheless, they coped with us for the best part of a year, at first.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I had expressed an interest in becoming an engineer, so they found work for me as an apprentice at a small tool-making factory, [INAUDIBLE] Precision Tool Making, in-- off Baker Street somewhere in London.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I went there every day.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And [NON-ENGLISH] went to school, and I think Eve may also have gone to school, or, or soon went to school.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We lived there for a year, and we met lots of [NON-ENGLISH] and [NON-ENGLISH] friends.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But generally, they couldn't really cope with us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Not only was there too many people in the flat, but financially they were not well off.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And eventually, the idea was that I should go somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the Jewish Refugees Committee in London made contact.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
